-- Azerbaijan Won’t Help Iran Attack, Hasanov Tells Media Forum
-- B y   Z u l f u g a r   A g a y e v
-- 2012-10-03T11:02:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-03/azerbaijan-won-t-help-iran-attack-hasanov-tells-media-forum.html
Azerbaijan  assured  Iran  it won’t
support military action against its neighbor, said Ali Hasanov,
head of the social and political department of President Ilham Aliyev’s office, the Media Forum news service reported.  “We are telling Iran unequivocally: Do not expect betrayal
from us,” Hasanov said in an  interview , according to Media
Forum. “We are telling them: We will not be used as a launching
ground in attacks against you.”  Energy-rich Azerbaijan, which has a population of 9.3
million, has a 756 km (470 mile) common border with Iran. Most
Azeris also share Iran’s Shiite religion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zulfugar Agayev in Baku at 
